      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:4:11:1",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ صَيْدِ الْحِيتَانِ وَ إِنْ لَمْ يُسَمَّ عَلَيْهِ فَقَالَ لَا بَأْسَ بِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I asked him<sup>asws</sup> about hunting the fish, and if he does not Name (<span class=\"iTxt\">Bismillah</span>) over it. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There is no problem with it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hammad from al-Halabiy who has said the following: “I once asked abu ‘ Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about catching fish without a mention of the name of Allah. He (the Imam) said, ‘It is not unlawful.’” "
        ]
      }
